content.description: Fun consistent crack. start at the bottom in the widish right crack place a larger piece and then face climb to the left crack and continue up as it goes from fingers to wide hands.
content.protection: BD .3 through 3 and an optional 4. If you have an extra 2 or 3 camalot it will be nice to throw in for a anchor for the belayer, if not there's a tree there that was partially still alive  that you can use .
content.location: This crack is up and right of the main north wall area. As you walk into the canyon this crack can easily be seen. break off from the main trail and bushwack across the wash and over to the other rim . cairns should lead you to the crack but if the not try and keep an eye on the rim and walk past the firs two rock outcroppings and it will be on the third one. theres a tree for a rap anchor or you can use a large boulder stack right by the edge

content.description: Starts in the corner crack to the right of Allez Lou.  Climb to the top of corner crack and traverse right to where there is a thin crack that takes gear from >.3-.75 BD.  This section is essentially face climbing with good traditional protection.  After the crack ends continue up a now bolted face through a couple harder moves to the anchor.  (There are 2 bolts for the anchor but there are currently no quicklinks for rappelling, should be up soon.  Climb up and left to Allez Lou for lowering or rappelling)
content.protection: One of each .3-.75.  One #3 for down low.  Three bolts on face to two bolt anchor.
content.location: This route shares the start of Delayed Gratification and is one of the furthest to the right on the north main wall.  Right of Allez Lou.

content.description: Solid face climbing with a couple of places for jams. stays in the corner for most of the climb. Decent climbing until the last few feet to access the final ledge,which is covered in decaying plant matter.
content.protection: Standard rack. Slung tree at the top. I did it with singles but was definitely running it out
content.location: corner/broken crack 5 feet to the left of Fogger.

content.description: This is one of the most obvious lines out here and a very fun route. It follows a vertical crack for 4 pitches. This route is in the shade all day.
Crux is passing the roof, hard to find hold and difficult right hand with scummy feet over roof.   Second crux is getting past the first bolt above the upper ledge.
content.protection: bolts, rap anchor or continue to top via other routes.
content.location: At left end of north-facing Rainbow Wall, just left of Remission's wide crack.  Look for a 4' roof @ 20' off the ground.

content.description: Start at slab below corner/roof 50' left of Allez Lou. Crux roof 15' off the ground takes thin nuts, committing move over the roof on finger jam. Fingers mostly to the top.

First crux is getting past the small roof.  Stay on the spine-like arete til you mantle and move right to the opposite arete.  Committing mantle gets you to the finishing jug.  Easy climbing leads to the top.
content.location: In center of the north main wall between Strongarm and Frogger.  Starts on brown slab to small roof 30' above.

content.description: Excellent corner, crack is very clean and takes all the pro you throw in it.  Face holds make this easier than it looks.  Look for a belay ledge at the 2nd roof on the left.
content.protection: fingers to wide as you want.
content.location: Large corner formed by Rainbow Buttress/Wall and North Walls.  Look for a black and brown corner; in the shade year round.

content.description: Stay just right of shadow play on the black face following weaknesses and intermittent cracks to overhung slot then easy rock to top; 2 rope rap from rap hangers just right of the top on Green Lantern.
wide crack just L of Transmission
Right of Mangina, lieback the flake to the roof, climb the face above: 100ft to two bolt anchor.
content.protection: 1 large cam will protect the easy approach climbing to the first bolt then 5 bolts to the ledge, once you gain the ledge clip a directional bolt and traverse left to rap anchor above Mangina.

climbs.name: Midori Corner
climbs.fa: M. Rangel, S. Sugimoto, S. Winkler

content.description:
The climb ascends a broken chimney/stemfest to an awkward bulge, gains a ledge then up the leaning dihedral with a widening crack to top. 

  The route begins off the trail on a 50' buttress with an easy 5th class crack on right or 5.9 finger crack in center.  Gain the large ledge, walk left to an oak tree for a belay.  Climb leftmost broken chimney, staying left to the obvious dihedral to top.
content.protection: sm to med nuts, doubles to #3 camalot, (1) #3.5, #4 camalot; gear belay.
content.location: As you get to the North Wall along the trail, look for a prominent roof with a hand crack @ 100' above.  This route is just left of it.  Rappel Impaired Rendition anchors w/double 60m ropes (visible just north of route); use caution when approaching anchors.

content.description: Right of Dirty Sanchez: climb the ramp to roof, remember to rest at the agave! 100ft to anchors.
content.protection: 2 bolts, fixed knife blade and gear to #1camalot

content.description: Getting thru the roof down low is juggy but the crux is a bit higher.
content.location: Look for the brown slab right of Strongarm and just left of the chimney.

content.description: Getting past the lip of the first roof is the first difficulty; passing the second small roof is harder.  Thin feet make the start a bear and getting the jug above the second roof is helpful.
content.location: This is the first route you see on the ledge trail of the Main Wall.  It is an obvious landmark, an 8' roof right over the trail.  Scramble up the pedestal/flake to the roof for the first bolt.

content.description: Do first pitch of Transmission (3 bolts and gear, 10d); go left from anchors to a crack for 10' and continue up and left thru overhung face (8 bolts and gear at start only, crux pitch, 11c); up steep face to exposed lieback arete finish; this can be bypassed by going on the arete for an easier finish (8 bolts, 10c). Rap route w/single 60m rope.
Fifty feet right of Allez Lou is a 130' face with a roof split by a crack @ 3/4 way up; face and thin crack to anchor. Approach from top or do a 30' approach pitch thru bushes to a ledge.
Around center of climb, getting pro in seems to be the hard part. Nice horizontals and great holds. Beautiful green lichen. Tim on the first ascent!
content.protection: Small C3/purple to .5 camalot; no bolts. Build gear anchor above near trail.
content.location: Located below the Main Wall trail; obvious bright green buttress below Dirty Sanchez. Walk down gully formed below Shadow Play.

content.description: Begin 30' right of Shadow Play on 45' of easy 5th class to first bolt. Climbing past the first bolt is the crux. Wander up easy rock to a steep juggy section then straight to the top on slab. Full route is approximately 150 feet.
Fun 'squeeze' chimney.  Finishes right on La Nariz anchors.
content.location: Chimney immediately left of La Nariz start.

content.description: Brown crack right of Red Zinger and left of Strongarm. Starts out easy then becomes a squeeze with a handcrack in the back. Squirm your way up @ 25' to a roof topping the crack. Go right for the anchors.
located north of the main wall about 150ft. climb the ramp to the corner past a roof to rap anchors 100ft.

Start is the same as "White Punks on Dope" and instead of moving to the right at the top of the easy corner continue strait up bolted face through delicate thin face moves.  Anchors are the same as Allez Lou.
content.protection: A couple of cams from .75-3.  4 Bolts to 2 bolt anchor.

content.description: Just 50' right of Green Lantern is a clean overhung face with a finger crack thru an overhang.  Brown and white rock with jugs and ever steeper finger locks make for a strenuous passage.
content.protection: finger sizes mostly to a #4 camalot up high.
content.location: Look for a brown slab just right of the prickly pear, climb easy crack to an overhung crack off the ledge.

content.description: Start at slab below corner/roof 50' left of Allez Lou. Crux roof 15' off the ground takes thin nuts, committing move over the roof on finger jam. Fingers mostly to the top.
North Wall starts when you get to the Main Wall, and extends to the route Submission.
